# Responsive design

TYPELY must work on three device classes:

- **Common monitors (≥1280px):** the default desktop layout.
- **Small laptops / Chromebooks (1280–1366 wide, ~768/800 tall):** the real
  constraint is *height*. It is handled by the existing
  `@media (max-height: 720px | 620px | 560px)` blocks. Keep the desktop width
  layout for these.
- **Phones (≤768px):** handled by the single consolidated **"RESPONSIVE PASS"
  section appended at the END of `src/styles/global.css`** — width-only
  `≤768 / ≤600 / ≤430` queries placed last so they win the cascade without
  editing the scattered earlier overrides.

Rules:
- Add new phone rules in that final section; do NOT regress the desktop or
  Chromebook layouts.
- Prefer fluid units (`clamp()`, `vw/vh`, `min()`/`max()`) over hard pixel
  offsets. Example: the login mascots are sized by
  `min(60vh, calc((50vw - 18rem) / 0.69))` so both scale together and flank the
  card at every width.
- No horizontal page scrollbar at any width (`overflow-x: hidden` safety ≤768px).
- The gameplay keyboard must fit the viewport width on phones (reduce per-key
  `min-width`, keep rows centred) — never let it overflow.
- Modals/popovers must scroll when taller than the viewport; buttons stay
  reachable.

Verify changes at 375×812 (phone), 1366×768 (Chromebook) and 1440×900 (monitor).
